title: 00165 Full Fan No Boot (Cold CPU)
message:
One power supply involved on ALL_SYS_PWRGD generation fails.
Can also be corrosion at U1950, or Q8150.
Check that area...

title: 00165 Full Fan No Boot (Cold CPU)
message: What do you mean by that first sentence?

title: 00165 Full Fan No Boot (Cold CPU)
message: A bad power supply can pulls down ALL_SYS_PWRGD...

title: 00165 Full Fan No Boot (Cold CPU)
message: Ahh. Ok. What would be an example of this?

title: 00165 Full Fan No Boot (Cold CPU)
message:
ALL_SYS_PWRGD is generated on page 59.
A bunch of resistors bring power good signals from several power supplies.
You can remove one by one, untill ALL_SYS_PWRGD goes high.
The last removed denotes the failing power supply.
You can start removing Q8150, which is not even necessary.
Be aware, do NOT remove R8167; is the pull-up resistor for ALL_SYS_PWRGD signal.
